law.text:
The board may:
Hire an executive director, set compensation appropriate for the administrative responsibilities of the position, and delegate to the executive director those duties for daily operation;
Appoint ad hoc committees, if necessary, to conduct the business of the board;
Hire legal counsel as needed;
Employ an administrative assistant or assistants to assist the executive director in the completion of daily activities and responsibilities of this chapter; and
Employ or contract with other persons as needed to carry out the work of the board.
